Definition: the property of being untamed and ferocious
Example: the coastline is littered with testaments to the savageness of the waters; a craving for barbaric splendor, for savagery and color and the throb of drums
Synonyms: adj, all, wild, savage, violent, noncivilized, inhumane, savagery, ferocity, the, property, of, being, untamed, and, ferocious, coastline, is, littered, with, testaments, to, waters, a, craving, for, barbaric, splendor, color, throb, drums
Category: noun.attribute
